(2337, 138, 'specifications', '<h2 class="panel-body">Key features</h2><ul><li>7 Are land (2 certificates)</li><li>770 m2 built area, consisting of 470m2 living, , 80m2 Garage partially lockable, 135m2 Deck, 75m2 pool.</li><li>Nature views of Gullys and trees, with a view of the south ocean from the Master bedroom.</li><li>Fully furnished with custom high end furnishings throughout. All fittings, appliances, Garden pots, decorations included, not personal goods.</li><li>Quiet no through road, 6m road in front.</li><li>5 bedrooms all with ensuite, 4 master size bedrooms all with built in robes and A/C’s and fans. 5<sup>th</sup> bedroom/office/maids quarters.</li><li>2 kitchens.</li><li>6 toilets.</li><li>Laundry and plenty of storage.</li><li>3 car garage.</li><li>Natural stone floors throughout, including stone imported specifically for this project.</li><li>250 m2 of Feature stone and timber walls.</li><li>Large 15m x 5m salt water infinity pool in Indian Natural Stone.</li><li>7m high old teak and glass doors throughout, around 100 doors allow the house to be fully open daytime, fully lockable night. All Henderson rails and rollers.</li><li>Exposed timber and weave ceiling covers the majority of the house as the main feature, including full covered walkway from parking to living area.</li><li>Quality built with quality fittings throughout. Grohe tapware, blum hardware, Henderson rail systems.</li><li>60,000 litre water tank and rain water collection system from roofing. Don’t need to buy water for more than 6 months of the year, water cost annually around $1,700 for full time family and staff.</li><li>Hi level electrical and plumbing infrastructure.</li><li>Skate bowl can be filled in with garden if it won’t be used.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>'),
