(4075, 206, 'specifications', '<h2 class="panel-body">Key features</h2><ul><li>10,7 are land (2 certificates)</li><li>770 m2 of build area, consisting of 470m2 of living, 80m2 of garage, 135m2 of sundeck and a 75m2 pool.</li><li>Natural views of the surrounding countryside with a view of the south ocean from the upper level.</li><li>Fully furnished with custom high-end furnishings throughout. Fittings, appliances, garden pots and decorations included.</li><li>6m road in front, which is a quiet no through road.</li><li>5 bedrooms all with ensuite, 4 master size bedrooms all with built-in robes and A/C’s and fans. 5<sup>th</sup> bedroom/office/maids quarters.</li><li>2 kitchens.</li><li>6 toilets.</li><li>Laundry and plenty of storage.</li><li>3 car garage.</li><li>Natural stone floors throughout, including rare stone imported specifically for this project.</li><li>250 m2 of feature stone and timber walls.</li><li>Large 15m x 5m salt water infinity pool in Indian natural stone.</li><li>7m high old teak and glass doors throughout, around 100 doors allow the house to be fully open daytime, fully lockable night. All rails and rollers are Henderson.</li><li>Exposed timber and weave ceiling covers the majority of the house as the main feature, including full covered walkway from parking to living area.</li><li>Quality built with quality fittings throughout. Grohe tapware, blum hardware, Henderson rail systems.</li><li>60,000 litre water tank and rain water collection system from roofing.</li><li>Top quality electrical and plumbing infrastructure.</li></ul>'),
